of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen the Imam says, \u2018Allah heard those who praise him,\u2019 then say, \u2018Our Lord, for you is praise.\u2019 If one\u2019s statement coincides with the statement of the angels, his previous sins will be forgiven.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12013,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/04\/repeat-adhan\/","url_meta":{"origin":33020,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Repeat what is said by the caller to prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 4, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhen you hear the call to prayer, say something similar to what the caller has said.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 611, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 383 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25822,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/01\/28\/allah-in-front-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":33020,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Allah in front of you when praying","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 28, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf one of you is in prayer, let him not spit in front of himself, for Allah is in front of him as he prays.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 398, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 547 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36702,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/07\/26\/dua-ala-mushrikin-uthaymeen\/","url_meta":{"origin":33020,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Qunut: The Prophet prays for reforming hardship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, when he said, \u201cAllah listened to those who praise Him,\u201d in the last cycle of evening prayer, he stood to supplicate, \u201cO Allah, save \u2018Ayyash ibn Abi Rabiah. O Allah, save Al-Walid ibn al-Walid. O Allah, save Salamah ibn\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37529,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/15\/4-takbeer-salat-janazah\/","url_meta":{"origin":33020,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Janazah: Four takbirat in the funeral prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 15, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings upon him, announced the news to people on the day the Negus died. The Prophet went out with them to the place of prayer, they stood in rows, and he exalted Allah with four exaltations. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1333, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36200,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/16\/istisqa-raising-hands-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":33020,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Istisqa: Raising hands to supplicate for rain","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 16, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would not raise his hands for any supplication except to pray for rain. He would raise them until we saw the skin of his armpits. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3565, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 895 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/33020","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\